02:09:47.498 --> 02:09:48.179
I don't know if it's going to be

02:09:48.198 --> 02:09:49.399
a pecking order that we see here.

02:09:49.920 --> 02:09:51.680
I have no problem with Kevin being at

02:09:51.720 --> 02:09:53.380
the top of the pyramid here,

02:09:53.680 --> 02:09:55.360
but we know where we keep on hiding

02:09:55.400 --> 02:09:57.980
rich, rich, rich, like in the background.

02:09:59.060 --> 02:10:00.101
Yeah.

02:10:00.341 --> 02:10:00.561
Yeah.

02:10:00.601 --> 02:10:04.603
What we do is finding though,

02:10:04.643 --> 02:10:05.823
that what we have is a whole lot

02:10:05.863 --> 02:10:06.622
of introverts too.

02:10:08.637 --> 02:10:10.738
And God seems to like introverts.

02:10:12.439 --> 02:10:14.740
And I know I don't come across as

02:10:14.780 --> 02:10:15.360
an introvert.

02:10:15.421 --> 02:10:16.942
And I know that, Kevin,

02:10:16.962 --> 02:10:18.301
you don't really come across as an

02:10:18.341 --> 02:10:19.103
introvert either.

02:10:19.622 --> 02:10:20.962
But I actually am an introvert.

02:10:21.042 --> 02:10:22.144
I was born an introvert.

02:10:22.884 --> 02:10:25.244
I just decided early in life as a

02:10:25.265 --> 02:10:29.087
young man that I didn't like being an

02:10:29.146 --> 02:10:31.307
introvert because the extroverts had all

02:10:31.347 --> 02:10:33.488
the pretty girls and they were they were.

02:10:35.287 --> 02:10:35.688
I didn't.

02:10:36.009 --> 02:10:37.529
And so I said, you know,

02:10:38.831 --> 02:10:40.452
I'm going to resolve this and I'm going

02:10:40.471 --> 02:10:41.432
to become an extrovert.

02:10:42.373 --> 02:10:43.574
And I transitioned to one,

02:10:43.595 --> 02:10:44.876
but I'm a natural introvert too.

02:10:44.935 --> 02:10:45.855
So I'm going to enjoy,

02:10:45.936 --> 02:10:48.377
we're all going to enjoy our rich time

02:10:48.418 --> 02:10:49.920
behind the scenes too,

02:10:50.100 --> 02:10:52.561
from time to time and take a step

02:10:52.601 --> 02:10:55.384
back and be out of the spotlight and

02:10:55.463 --> 02:10:58.426
just enjoying being together in small

02:10:58.445 --> 02:10:58.686
groups.

02:10:58.747 --> 02:11:00.448
I think that's the thing that Yahowah is

02:11:00.488 --> 02:11:01.269
looking forward to.

02:11:01.948 --> 02:11:02.630
It's small groups.

02:11:04.012 --> 02:11:06.715
You know, one-on-one, one-on-two or three,

02:11:07.135 --> 02:11:07.836
going off to,

02:11:08.195 --> 02:11:09.837
when we go off and explore a different

02:11:09.917 --> 02:11:12.338
galaxy or even this galaxy,

02:11:13.338 --> 02:11:14.939
I think what he's looking forward to doing

02:11:15.640 --> 02:11:17.481
is doing it with a very small group

02:11:17.521 --> 02:11:19.222
of us, an intimate setting.

02:11:20.423 --> 02:11:21.664
I think, yeah, I was an introvert,

02:11:21.725 --> 02:11:26.627
and I think he's attracting people who are

02:11:28.429 --> 02:11:29.550
somewhat introverted as well.

02:11:29.590 --> 02:11:30.489
He does not like big,

02:11:30.610 --> 02:11:32.391
it's obvious God does not like big crowds.

02:11:32.412 --> 02:11:32.492
Yeah.

02:11:33.216 --> 02:11:35.358
But field trips with Yahowah are going to

02:11:35.398 --> 02:11:37.118
be just off the charts.

02:11:37.637 --> 02:11:38.838
Yeah, imagine the field trips.

02:11:39.059 --> 02:11:39.338
Oh, yeah.

02:11:41.378 --> 02:11:41.538
Yeah,

02:11:41.639 --> 02:11:43.460
and the beauty of all of that on

02:11:43.539 --> 02:11:46.860
some of these field trips is that we

02:11:46.900 --> 02:11:49.921
can do our job six days a week,

02:11:50.341 --> 02:11:52.322
seven days a week in terms of teaching

02:11:52.722 --> 02:11:55.603
and be diligent in our teaching and still

02:11:56.184 --> 02:11:57.503
take a month off in a second.

02:12:00.520 --> 02:12:03.641
We could take a year voyage with Yahowah

02:12:04.082 --> 02:12:07.404
to a faraway galaxy and explore life and

02:12:07.463 --> 02:12:11.247
everything on it and have that time play

02:12:11.346 --> 02:12:13.408
out as if it were the most fun

02:12:13.427 --> 02:12:16.310
year of our lives and we could be

02:12:16.350 --> 02:12:16.970
gone a second.

02:12:18.091 --> 02:12:18.990
That's kind of freaky.

02:12:19.692 --> 02:12:21.613
It's kind of freaky, isn't it?

02:12:21.693 --> 02:12:22.613
Eat this MC squared.

02:12:22.632 --> 02:12:25.574
Yeah.

02:12:25.635 --> 02:12:27.115
Well, on light

02:12:27.847 --> 02:12:29.729
On a photon of light, time simply is.

02:12:30.850 --> 02:12:33.131
All time exists simultaneously.

02:12:33.572 --> 02:12:35.833
So you will be able to maneuver in

02:12:35.894 --> 02:12:38.395
time and therefore we'll be able to

02:12:38.555 --> 02:12:42.297
experience things where time moves at a

02:12:42.338 --> 02:12:43.739
pace that we're comfortable with.

02:12:44.100 --> 02:12:45.780
We can slow time or speed it up.

02:12:45.881 --> 02:12:50.224
And when you're dealing with an infinite

02:12:50.283 --> 02:12:51.305
amount of time,

02:12:52.028 --> 02:12:53.828
it really doesn't matter how much time you

02:12:53.868 --> 02:12:55.229
spend doing anything, does it?

02:12:55.250 --> 02:12:56.630
No, yeah.

02:12:56.649 --> 02:12:58.931
You have no less time to spend no

02:12:58.971 --> 02:13:02.993
matter how much time you have spent.

02:13:03.354 --> 02:13:04.014
And you don't run out of time.

02:13:04.054 --> 02:13:04.173
Right.

02:13:04.215 --> 02:13:05.414
And it's kind of already done.

02:13:05.475 --> 02:13:06.916
And what you've already done,

02:13:07.155 --> 02:13:09.077
what you're doing is kind of already done.

02:13:09.858 --> 02:13:10.217
Yes.

02:13:10.677 --> 02:13:13.859
And the beauty of it is that it's

02:13:13.939 --> 02:13:15.860
never going to be boring because we will

02:13:15.900 --> 02:13:17.601
never be unemployed.

02:13:18.002 --> 02:13:18.221
Right.

02:13:20.021 --> 02:13:23.664
Even once that final remnant after the

02:13:23.685 --> 02:13:26.648
thousand years is either all covenant or

02:13:27.087 --> 02:13:30.971
gone or whatever God's disposition is at

02:13:30.992 --> 02:13:31.432
that time,

02:13:31.512 --> 02:13:32.974
once we've judged all the people that need

02:13:33.014 --> 02:13:34.475
to be judged and we've taken care of

02:13:34.515 --> 02:13:35.275
all the business,

02:13:36.677 --> 02:13:39.300
even in eternity off the planet,

02:13:39.739 --> 02:13:40.921
we're going to continue to work.

02:13:41.804 --> 02:13:42.824
God values work.

02:13:43.426 --> 02:13:44.827
He wants us to accomplish something.

02:13:45.367 --> 02:13:47.588
It is what makes for an interesting

02:13:47.628 --> 02:13:48.309
relationship.

02:13:48.390 --> 02:13:51.051
It's what causes God to be infinite.

02:13:51.072 --> 02:13:53.153
Do you know that God can't be infinite

02:13:53.373 --> 02:13:54.073
unless he grows?

02:13:54.094 --> 02:13:55.194
You're right.

02:13:55.215 --> 02:13:55.755
I understand.

02:13:55.975 --> 02:13:56.235
Yes.

02:13:56.336 --> 02:13:56.576
Yeah.

02:13:56.636 --> 02:13:58.837
Infinity is impossible without growth.

02:14:00.458 --> 02:14:02.761
And when you are God and can know

02:14:03.641 --> 02:14:04.622
and do anything,

02:14:05.884 --> 02:14:07.125
the only way you can grow is through

02:14:07.145 --> 02:14:08.244
relationships like this.

02:14:08.466 --> 02:14:10.868
So we actually contribute something of

02:14:10.908 --> 02:14:11.188
value.

02:14:12.130 --> 02:14:14.110
We're going to be tremendously valued by

02:14:14.171 --> 02:14:14.430
God.

02:14:15.851 --> 02:14:19.833
And it's just a marvelous thing that we're

02:14:19.873 --> 02:14:19.974
in.

02:14:20.234 --> 02:14:20.333
Well,

02:14:20.354 --> 02:14:23.695
we've gone even fifteen minutes past our

02:14:23.735 --> 02:14:24.576
hour, two hours.

02:14:25.456 --> 02:14:27.577
So it's been a fun family hour, though,

02:14:27.617 --> 02:14:31.118
hasn't it?

02:14:31.639 --> 02:14:32.460
Great show.

02:14:32.479 --> 02:14:32.640
Yeah.

02:14:33.060 --> 02:14:33.720
I've enjoyed this.

02:14:33.760 --> 02:14:39.703
And the moment that I went to the

02:14:39.722 --> 02:14:40.783
body of twelve,

02:14:41.868 --> 02:14:44.190
Because my concern was, these people,

02:14:44.350 --> 02:14:45.131
are they right?

02:14:45.332 --> 02:14:48.055
